Extensions
Get familiar with the concept of extensions and how to use them in your project. Understanding Extensions
Learn how to use extensions in your project
Using read extensions in React
Any extension that reads from the blockchain can be used with
useReadContract
. The extension function itself be passed as the first argument, and the extension's parameters must be passed as the second argument. import
{ getContract }
from
"thirdweb"
;
import
{ useReadContract }
from
"thirdweb/react"
;
import
{ getOwnedNFTs }
from
"thirdweb/extensions/erc721"
;
const
contract
=
getContract
({
client,
chain,
address:
"0x..."
,
});
const
MyComponent
=
()
=>
{
const
ownedNFTs
=
useReadContract
(getOwnedNFTs, {
contract,
address:
"0x..."
,
});
};
